etymologies: 1950s. From phen- + met- + -r-, linking element + azine

definitions: A sympathomimetic agent with stimulant effects on the central nervous system similar to those of dexamphetamine, used chiefly as an appetite suppressant.

notes.text: Chemical name: 3-methyl-2-phenylmorpholine, C₁₁H₁₅NO. A trademark for this drug is Preludin.
